[SN]TITLE[SN]
WW2 archive: Ulster Home Guard recruitment video

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A new BBC Radio Ulster documentary, Not Dad's Army - Northern Ireland's Home Guard, tells the story of the controversial Ulster Home Guard.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
27 February 2015 Last updated at 06:46 GMT
In this recruitment video from 1942, Major General V.H.B Majendie, commanding officer for Northern Ireland, appeals for support for the defence force.
Used with permission from the Police Museum of Northern Ireland.
Not Dad's Army - Northern Ireland's Home Guard will be broadcast on BBC Radio Ulster at 12:30 GMT on Sunday 1 March 2015. It will then be available on BBC IPlayer radio.
